                            global sign languages.</li>
                        <li><strong>Letter E:</strong> The 'E' in ASL is distinguished by its tightly closed formation,
                            emphasizing precision in hand positioning. It also plays a symbolic role in ASL poetry and
                            storytelling.</li>
                        <li><strong>Letter F:</strong> The 'F' handshape in ASL uniquely represents both the letter and
                            the number 9. This dual role exemplifies the efficiency and adaptability of ASL.</li>
                        <li><strong>Letter G:</strong> The 'G' in ASL, often used in signs related to pointing or
                            direction, is crucial for clear communication. Its precision highlights the language's
                            expressiveness.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Each of these letters contributes to the expressive capacity and cultural richness of American
                        Sign Language, making them integral to both spelling and communication.</p>
