                <h2>Letter D</h2>
                <p>The letter 'D' in ASL represents a circular shape formed by the thumb and index finger, resembling
                    the uppercase 'D'. It's important for both clarity in communication and as a foundational sign in
                    the language.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Start with Your Hand Open:</strong> Begin with your hand open, palm facing away from
                        you, fingers together and straight.</li>
                    <li><strong>Curl Your Fingers:</strong> Curl your fingers into a circle, touching your thumb with
                        the tips of your fingers, forming the shape of a 'D'.</li>
                    <li><strong>Position Your Thumb:</strong> Keep your thumb crossed over the index finger, completing
                        the circle.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Practice this sign to ensure that you are understood when communicating with others in ASL. The
                    distinct round shape of the 'D' is a critical element to master.</p>
